From 6e3f5b2c1a4d8e7f9c3b5a2d1e4f7c8b6a5d3e2f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 18:05:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] arm: airoha: an7563-evb: enable CMD_ARHT_FLASH

Turn on CONFIG_CMD_ARHT_FLASH=y in the AN7563 EVB defconfig so the
Airoha BMT-aware `arht_flash` command (added in
602-cmd-add-arht_flash-airoha-bmt-utility.patch) is available from
the U-Boot prompt on this board.  AN7563 EVB is the only Airoha
board today that opts into the BMT layer (see
601-airoha-7563-evb-enable-bmt.patch), so this is also the only
board where the command is meaningful; other Airoha boards
(AN7581 / AN7583 / EN7523) keep the option off.

The two subcommands enabled by this:

  arht_flash dumpbmt           - dump in-RAM BMT/BBT state
  arht_flash forceeraseall yes - factory-reset the chip, ATF will
                                 rebuild BMT/BBT on next boot

Signed-off-by: Ray Liu <ray.xy.liu@gmail.com>
---
 configs/an7563_evb_defconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
+++ b/configs/an7563_evb_defconfig
@@ -26,6 +26,7 @@
 CONFIG_CMD_BOOTMENU=y
 # CONFIG_CMD_ELF is not set
 # CONFIG_CMD_XIMG is not set
+CONFIG_CMD_ARHT_FLASH=y
 CONFIG_CMD_BIND=y
 CONFIG_CMD_GPIO=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MTD=y
